The paper deals with the problem of few-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science. The paper proposes a novel data hallucination model that utilizes saliency maps to generate additional data from limited existing samples. This involves the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
